page.title: 14Manor Farm Dairy
page.content: Manor farm dairy has cows, sheep and horses. They have 350 cows and 100 sheep also two pet horses. A cow eats potatoes, carrots and pancakes. A cow does not give 12 months milk after having a calf it only gives 2 months milk.Then when the calf is about 12 days old they put them on the market to be sold.The cow gives between 15 and 45 litres of milk a day. To keep crops and animals they have 300 acres of land. The sort of things they grow are carrots , potatoes and they give it to the shops and the cows.Silage is made by cutting the grass and then they bring it into a shed and cover the grass up.They then put a chemical on and leave it for 6 weeks.Their guard dog's name is Jacob and sometimes the dog rounds the sheep up.
